Instllation
sudo apt-get -y install git-core
or
sudo apt -y install git

Clone from github
git clone git@github.com:linuxkay/tools.git

Preparation for user
mkdir git-dir
cd git-dir
git clone git@github.com:linuxkay/tools.git
git clone git@github.com:linuxkay/ski-resorts-crawler

Adding file
cd git-dir
vim or touch file
git add file
git commit file
git commit -am "file added"
git push origin master

Pull master
git pull origin master

Status
git status

Other stuff
git config --global user.name "linuxkay"
git config --global user.email "youremailaddress"
### not need it 2019/9/4 --> git config --global push.default simple

Create repository in github.com manually by going there in browser.
after that

mkdir Git
cd Git
git init
##### not need it 2019/9/4--> git branch

echo "# raspberrypi_systemctl" >> README.md
git init
git add README.md
git commit -m "first commit"
git remote add origin git@github.com:linuxkay/raspberrypi_systemctl.git
git push -u origin master


## rename files in git
use
git mv originalfile newfilename
